  "texts": [
    "In the context of transformers, tokenization breaks down sentences into tokens, often words or subwords.",
    "Each token corresponds to a specific index in a vocabulary list, allowing the model to work with the text numerically.",
    "Tokenization is a crucial first step in transforming natural language into a format that a model can understand, making it an integral part of how transformers handle input sequences and extract meaning.",
    "An embedding is a numerical representation of tokens (words or subwords) that encodes their meanings in the form of vectors -arrays of numbers.",
    "These vectors place words in a multi-dimensional space where similar words are positioned closer together, helping models like transformers understand relationships and context between tokens."
  ],
